        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 6:24PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Buchanan to John Tanner State Park, and moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Villa Rica, Bremen, Temple, Mount Zion, Abilene,
Draketown, Lake Val-Do-Mar, John Tanner State Park, Treasure Lake,
Bowdon Junction, and New Georgia.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
